Quote:  He made his name during his first day on the place by his masterly handling of a "break" of lambs. Only those who have had experience of dealing with "breaking" Merino lambs at tailing time can appreciate the test for man and dog. <i>Ibid.</i> p. 153.Break : Lamb-break:... Great care must be exercised, as a false move by man or dog will have the lambs, ever on their toes, stampeding or breaking.
